properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 6 at 4:01AM EST until February 8 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southwest to west winds 15 to 25
kt with gusts up to 40 kt and seas 7 to 10 feet expected. For
the Small Craft Advisory, south winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up
to 30 kt and seas 5 to 8 feet expected.

* WHERE...The New Jersey and Delaware Atlantic coastal waters.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 AM Friday to 1 AM EST
Saturday. The strongest winds are expected to occur Friday
afternoon and evening. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 PM
this afternoon to 6 AM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
